Package: gwplotting
Title: Utilities for plotting statistics from genome-wide analyses
Version: 1.0.1
Authors@R: person("Nicholas", "VanKuren", email = "nwvankuren@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: 
    This package is designed to read in the results of common analyses 
    of genome-wide diversity, divergence, and association and plot them. It 
    contains functions to read in the results files from a variety of sources 
    and analyses, to reorder the results according to chromosomes or scaffold 
    lengths, and to plot those results.
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.5),
    ggplot2,
    tidyverse
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: 
    readr,
    tibble,
    stringr,
    tidyselect,
    purrr
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
Suggests: 
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
